<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Vim on sytranvn.dev</title><link>https://sytranvn.dev/tags/vim/</link><description>Recent content in Vim on sytranvn.dev</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 14 Jan 2025 11:25:29 +0700</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://sytranvn.dev/tags/vim/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Vi Everything</title><link>https://sytranvn.dev/posts/vi-everything/</link><pubDate>Tue, 14 Jan 2025 11:25:29 +0700</pubDate><guid>https://sytranvn.dev/posts/vi-everything/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s the list of couple places that I enable &lt;code&gt;vi&lt;/code&gt; mode.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bash shell
&lt;code&gt;set -o vi&lt;/code&gt; I always enable bash movement mode in my &lt;code&gt;.bashrc&lt;/code&gt; file.
With it set, I can switch between normal mode and edit mode by pressing &lt;code&gt;ESC&lt;/code&gt;.
Editing works as any normal shell, but when switching to normal mode, I can
use &lt;code&gt;vi&lt;/code&gt; movement keys like &lt;code&gt;j, k, h, l, w, b, e, $, ^&lt;/code&gt;, editing current
line is also faster by using selectors such as &lt;code&gt;cw, dw, C, D...&lt;/code&gt;. One important
note is that we are using &lt;code&gt;vi&lt;/code&gt; mode, not &lt;code&gt;vim&lt;/code&gt;, so selectors like &lt;code&gt;ciw, caw, ci(&lt;/code&gt; does not work.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Nvim External Commands</title><link>https://sytranvn.dev/posts/nvim-external-commands/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2024 11:07:52 +0700</pubDate><guid>https://sytranvn.dev/posts/nvim-external-commands/</guid><description>&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:!{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Execute &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;, display output&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:r !{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Execute &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;, insert output to current current cursor position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:w !{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pipe current buffer to &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:.!{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Execute &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;, replace current line with output&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:%!{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Execute &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;, replace entire buffer with output&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;:&amp;lt;&amp;#39;,&amp;#39;&amp;gt;!{cmd}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Execute &lt;code&gt;cmd&lt;/code&gt;, replace current selection output&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>